The paper focuses on a specific problem in software engineering, namely exception handling in mobile app development. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the challenges of API libraries and documentation, which suggests cs.PL (Programming Languages) as a possible category. The empirical evaluation of the proposed techniques involves analyzing code snippets, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Development). The paper specifically addresses issues in mobile app development, indicating cs.MOB (Mobile Computing) as another possible category. Finally, the proposed techniques involve code recommendation, which could be considered a form of artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category.
